channel.title: Eclipse SVN Problem
channel.description: I have a SVN setup for RSCEmulation with one username, but I have another project that I need to work with a SVN with a different username but the problem is, the second project is using the first projects login credentials. How do I 'forget' these or add more?

item.title: Eclipse SVN Problem
item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

Kryptix:

I have a SVN setup for RSCEmulation with one username, but I have another project that I need to work with a SVN with a different username but the problem is, the second project is using the first projects login credentials. How do I ‘forget’ these or add more?

I’ve never had luck getting any sort of versioning system to work properly with eclipse. So what I normally do is setup the repository via terminal, then refresh the project in eclipse. When I had a versioning system installed in eclipse, it would refresh with the new data.
